<div class="container">
  <h1>Judoscale Test Application</h1>

  <div class="card">
    <h2>Load Testing Tools</h2>
    <p>Use these tools to test Judoscale autoscaling capabilities:</p>

    <div>
      <div class="section">
        <h3>Slow Endpoint</h3>
        <p>This endpoint sleeps for a specified number of seconds before responding.</p>
        <div>
          <a href="/load_test/slow?seconds=5" class="button button-blue">
            Test (5 seconds)
          </a>
          <a href="/load_test/slow?seconds=10" class="button button-blue">
            Test (10 seconds)
          </a>
          <a href="/load_test/slow?seconds=20" class="button button-blue">
            Test (20 seconds)
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="section">
        <h3>Concurrent Slow Endpoint</h3>
        <p>This endpoint creates multiple threads that each sleep for a specified duration.</p>
        <div>
          <a href="/load_test/concurrent_slow?threads=3&seconds=5" class="button button-green">
            Test (3 threads, 5 seconds)
          </a>
          <a href="/load_test/concurrent_slow?threads=5&seconds=10" class="button button-green">
            Test (5 threads, 10 seconds)
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="section">
        <h3>Background Jobs</h3>
        <p>This endpoint enqueues background jobs that each run for a specified duration.</p>
        <div>
          <a href="/load_test/enqueue_jobs?count=10&seconds=10" class="button button-orange">
            Enqueue 10 jobs (10 seconds each)
          </a>
          <a href="/load_test/enqueue_jobs?count=20&seconds=15" class="button button-orange">
            Enqueue 20 jobs (15 seconds each)
          </a>
          <a href="/load_test/enqueue_jobs?count=50&seconds=20" class="button button-orange">
            Enqueue 50 jobs (20 seconds each)
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h2>Documentation</h2>
    <p>For more detailed information on testing Judoscale autoscaling, please refer to the <code>JUDOSCALE_TESTING.md</code> file in the project root.</p>

    <h3>Quick Commands</h3>
    <div class="code-block">
<pre>
# Run the web request load test script (targets remote server by default)
bin/test_autoscaling.rb

# Run with custom parameters
bin/test_autoscaling.rb --concurrency 40 --requests 150 --sleep 20

# Test against local server
bin/test_autoscaling.rb --url http://localhost:3000/load_test/slow

# Run the job queue load test script (targets remote server by default)
bin/test_job_queue.rb

# Run with custom parameters
bin/test_job_queue.rb --count 100 --duration 20 --batches 10

# Test against local server
bin/test_job_queue.rb --url http://localhost:3000/load_test/enqueue_jobs

# Run the combined load test (web requests + job queue)
bin/test_combined.rb

# Run with custom parameters
bin/test_combined.rb --web-concurrency 40 --web-requests 150 --job-count 100 --job-batches 10

# Test against local server
bin/test_combined.rb --url http://localhost:3000

# Manual testing with curl
curl "https://judoscale-test.onrender.com/load_test/slow?seconds=10"
curl "https://judoscale-test.onrender.com/load_test/concurrent_slow?threads=5&seconds=10"
curl "https://judoscale-test.onrender.com/load_test/enqueue_jobs?count=20&seconds=15"
</pre>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
